# Nexus Frontend Implementation

Nexus is a **mobile-first PWA** for lifting, sleep, nutrition, and habits. Offline resilience is a core constraint—avoid UI flows that assume uninterrupted network or break caching and sync assumptions without an explicit product decision.

## Stack boundaries

- **SPA:** React 19 + TypeScript + **Vite** + **react-router-dom**. Do not assume Next.js, SSR, or RSC patterns unless the repo gains a Next app.
- **Styling:** Tailwind utility classes on **`className`**, composed from **shadcn/ui primitives** in [`src/shared/ui/`](src/shared/ui/) and **semantic design tokens** in [`src/styles/global.css`](src/styles/global.css). Keep `global.css` limited to Tailwind layers and tokens; avoid new scattered CSS files unless the codebase already uses a shared pattern in `src/shared/` or app-level styles.
- **State:** TanStack React Query for server state; Zustand for offline-oriented and cache-oriented client state—follow slice boundaries in `.cursor/rules/01-tech-stack.mdc`.
- **Architecture:** Respect Feature-Sliced Design imports and public APIs (`.cursor/rules/02-fsd.mdc`). UI code belongs in `src/pages/`, `src/features/`, `src/entities/`, or `src/shared/`—and in additional FSD layers such as widgets when those slices exist—never violate upward imports.

## Components and TypeScript

- Use **function components** and hooks only.
- Define **Props** interfaces or types (or inline typed props) for exported components; prefer **`interface` for object shapes** used across exports.
- Prefer **readable code** over micro-optimizations unless profiling shows a hotspot.
- Prefer **early returns** for guard clauses (loading, missing data, feature flags) so the happy-path JSX stays shallow.
- Match **existing formatting** in `src/` (quotes, semicolons, import style) and pass **`npm run lint`**.

## Design system

### Stack

- **Tokens:** [`src/styles/global.css`](src/styles/global.css) — `:root` / `.dark` CSS variables mapped via `@theme inline` into Tailwind color utilities.
- **Primitives:** shadcn/ui **New York** style in [`src/shared/ui/`](src/shared/ui/), configured via [`components.json`](components.json).
- **Class merging:** always use **`cn()`** from [`src/shared/lib/utils.ts`](src/shared/lib/utils.ts) (`clsx` + `tailwind-merge`).
- **Icons:** `lucide-react`.

### Semantic colors

- **Do** use token utilities: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-primary`, `text-destructive`, `border-input`, `bg-primary`, etc.
- **Don't** use raw palette utilities (`text-slate-*`, `bg-zinc-*`, `text-gray-*`, `text-amber-*`, …) in `src/**/*.tsx` — they break dark mode and bypass the token system.

### Primitives first

- Import interactive and layout primitives from **`@/shared/ui`** (`Button`, `Card`, `Input`, `Form`, `Alert`, `Dialog`, …).
- Use component **variants** (`Button` `variant`/`size`, `Alert` `variant="destructive"`) instead of hand-rolled button or alert styles.
- Add new primitives via `npx shadcn@latest add <name>` (respects `components.json` aliases); export from [`src/shared/ui/index.ts`](src/shared/ui/index.ts).

### Layout

- App shell ([`src/app/App.tsx`](src/app/App.tsx)) owns viewport layout: `min-h-dvh`, `max-w-md mx-auto px-4`.
- Pages should not redefine full-viewport width; compose content inside the shell.

### Page composition (auth and form screens)

- Wrap content in **`Card`** + **`CardHeader`** + **`CardContent`**.
- Page title: `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight`.
- Secondary copy: `text-sm text-muted-foreground`.
- Links: `font-medium text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline`.
- Section spacing: `space-y-6` / `space-y-3`.

### Loading and error states

- **Loading:** centered `min-h-[40vh]` block; optional `Loader2` with `text-muted-foreground`; `role="status"` + `aria-live="polite"` when announcing progress (see [`AuthCallbackPage`](src/pages/auth-callback-page/AuthCallbackPage.tsx)).
- **Errors:** prefer **`Alert variant="destructive"`** with `AlertDescription`; inline fallback `text-destructive` / `text-muted-foreground` only for minimal inline copy.

### Dark mode

- Theme is class-based (`.dark` on `<html>`) via [`src/shared/lib/theme.ts`](src/shared/lib/theme.ts).
- Rely on semantic tokens; add `dark:` overrides only when extending primitives, matching patterns in `src/shared/ui/*`.

## Styling conventions

- Prefer **Tailwind** utilities for layout, spacing, typography, and states (`focus:`, `disabled:`, `dark:` when used consistently).
- For **conditional `className`**, use **`cn()`** from `@/shared/lib`—avoid long nested ternaries.
- Accept **`className?: string`** on reusable UI and merge with primitives via `cn(base, className)`.

## Events and naming

- Name user-event callbacks with a **`handle` prefix** where they represent behaviors wired from JSX (for example `handleSubmit`, `handleClick`, `handleKeyDown`). Inner helpers may stay private without the prefix if they are not passed as props.

## Accessibility

- Prefer **semantic HTML** (`button`, `a`, `label`, headings) before custom roles.
- Associate controls with labels: **`htmlFor` / `id`**, **`aria-labelledby`** / **`aria-describedby`** when headings or helper text establish context.
- For **custom interactive** surfaces (non-native buttons and links), support **keyboard** interaction (`Enter`/`Space` where appropriate), visible **focus**, and **disabled** state—do not default to **`tabIndex={0}`** on non-interactive wrappers (avoid sabotaging focus order).
- Mirror WCAG-minded patterns from the [ARIA authoring practices](https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/) when building dialogs, menus, or disclosure widgets.

## Product-specific cautions

- **Offline-first:** avoid UX that hard-requires network for core journaling flows without messaging or graceful degradation.
- **Secrets:** never embed Supabase keys or tokens in UI code; use **`import.meta.env`** per Vite (see [`.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc`](.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc)).
- **Auth-sensitive surfaces:** avoid leaking PII in logs, error copy, or analytics hooks.

## Completeness

- Deliver **complete** UI paths: loading, empty, error, and success where applicable—no `TODO` stubs or placeholder branches (aligned with `.cursor/rules/03-agent-boundaries.mdc`).
